text:
- Every commander, card, tribe, and theme page are now just "saved searches"/cached from advanced search

- New page: Advanced Query
   - this new page will have all of the options for how to filter down decks.
   - The current criteria should be: deck overall price (min, max), color identity OR specific commander, type counts (min, max), mentions of a specific phrases (count flying decks), subtype (curse, aura, equip) counts (min, max), key word count (min, max) (multiple?), includes these N cards.
   - As you enter in different values for each, you should get a preview on how many decks will be returned in your query, relatively live. It would be awesome if the tally results just got populated every time the query form was changed.

- New feature on tally pages: filter cards by criteria.
   - I imagine this menu being near the top of right before the card results start.
   - It would allow users to only see results based on their criteria. The criteria should be:
       - CMC
       - Color
       - Price (min, max)
       - Release date (min)
       - Type
       - Subtype / Tribe
